    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#openo-jmr1978-1979"/>, pp. <citedRange>228-299</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>37.1676</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>077800</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#siciliano2006"/>, p. <citedRange>421</citedRange>, fig. 16</bibl>, whence (as unpublished)
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>56.2032.4</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>175</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2020c"/>, pp. <citedRange>315-316</citedRange>, fig. 322</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.46</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Θεμίσων">Θεμίσων</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἄριστις" type="patronymic">Ἀρίστιος</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <rdg resp="#openo-jmr1978-1979">Θεμίσω<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <rdg resp="#openo-jmr1978-1979">Ἀρίστιο<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Thémisôn fils d'Aristis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Themison son of Aristis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Themison figlio di Aristis.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>For the <foreign rend="italic">editio princeps</foreign>, Reynolds saw the base still partly buried, whence the restorations at the end of both lines (so did also the Thorns); 
                    Siciliano's photograph (after unearthing of the base) shows that the inscription is complete.</p>
	           <p>For a dedication by the same man, see <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr016900</ref>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
